               <head>Collection of historical writings of Elijah Capsali</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070393" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>Various historical writings of Elijah Capsali. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="2r" to="343v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Seder Eliyahu zuta</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">סדר אליהו זוטא</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>A detailed account of the history of the Ottoman Empire, beginning with Mehmed II, and continuing to 1523. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Appended are two additional pieces: the first entitled 'Koaḥ ha-Shem', and treats on the plague in Crete in 1523 (folios 270v-292r); the second, 'Hasde ha-Shem', is an account of the rebellion of Ahmad Shaitan against sultan Soloman in 1524, and the deliverance of the Cairene Jews from the destruction (folios 292v-337r). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>At the end, there is an elegy, in rhymed prose, on notable men who died in the plague described in Koaḥ ha-Shem, followed by thanksgiving for the author's deliverance from it, and an account of the origin of his literary work (folios 337r-343v). </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName key="viaf.org/viaf/281275390" xml:lang="en">Capsali, Elijah, -1555</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName key="viaf.org/viaf/281275390" xml:lang="he">קפשלי, אליהו בן אלקנה</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85100947">
                     
                     
                     
